4 Section 901. A. There is hereby created a Long-Range Capital
5 Planning Commission to advise and assist the Legislature in
6 providing for real property capital facility needs for this state.
7 The Commission shall consist of nine (9) members as follows:
8 1. Three members appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the
9 Senate;
10 2. Three members appointed by the Speaker of the House of
11 Representatives; and
12 3. Three members appointed by the Governor.
13 All appointees shall be from the public at large. Within thirty
14 (30) days of July 1, 2013, the appointing authorities shall appoint
15 new members to the Commission; provided, a member serving on July 1,
16 2013, may be reappointed if he or she is otherwise qualified. Of
17 the members initially appointed by each appointing authority after
18 July 1, 2013, one shall be appointed for a one-year term, one shall
19 be appointed for a two-year term and one shall be appointed for a
20 three-year term. Thereafter, their successors shall be appointed
21 for four-year terms. Any vacancy shall be filled for the remainder
22 of the unexpired term in the same manner as the original
23 appointment. The appointing authorities shall appoint members who
24 possess knowledge, skills and abilities to perform the duties of the
SB1991 HFLR Page 15
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

